MySQL:5.7.25!


＊if u wanna use mysqldump to import database in mysql server locally, then try this part!

FIRST:

Login into your mysql server, and execute 「set FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS=0; 」 to close FK check. 

Pleae create database named "literature" and its format must be "utf8mb4". To see how to set up, we can reference instructions as below:

https://blog.csdn.net/boycycyzero/article/details/42879911


After that, log out.

>>> cd /Database/YouAlreadyHaveLocalMySQL/

>>> mysqldump -u youraccount -p literature < back_literature.sql 

SECOND:

Login into your mysql server, and 「set FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS=1;」.

>>> use  literature;

>>> source back_literature.sql 


Now, we complete data  import!


THIRD:

please modify "ChineseLiterature/ChineseLiterature/settings.py" and "ChineseLiterature/literature/views.py" if your mysql account info differentiates from default:

# settings.py
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
        'NAME': 'literature',
        'USER':'root',    <-----------------------
        'PASSWORD':'1234', <-----------------------
        'HOST':'127.0.0.1',
        'PORT':'3306',
        'OPTIONS': {'charset':'utf8mb4'},
    }
}

#views.py
conn = pymysql.connect('localhost',port=3306,「user='root',passwd='1234'」,charset='utf8',db='literature')



>>> cd ChineseLiterature/

>>> python manage.py runserver

Now, we can enjoy service by typing 「localhost:8000/bookInfo/」!

-----------------------------------------

＊if u wanna see how is going on when executing writeDataToDatabase_*.py , then try this part!

FIRST:

Pleae create database named "literature" and its format must be "utf8mb4". To see how to set up, we can reference instructions as below:

https://blog.csdn.net/boycycyzero/article/details/42879911


SECOND:


Synchronize this database by executing some commands in Django project folder.

>>> cd ChineseLiterature/

>>> find . -path "*/migrations/*.py" -not -name "__init__.py" -delete
>>> find . -path "*/migrations/*.pyc"  -delete

>>> python manage.py makemigrations
>>> python manage.py migrate

Now, django ORM help us to create tables we need according to models.py!

And, we can execute those writeDataToDatabase_*.py to see the conditions about inserting data into tables!


(Approximately 40 minutes it will take us to complete four tables. Under the SSD disk circumstance, time consuming will be declined! )

THIRD:

after completing data insert,

please modify "ChineseLiterature/ChineseLiterature/settings.py" and "ChineseLiterature/literature/views.py" if your mysql account info differentiates from default:

# settings.py
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
        'NAME': 'literature',
        'USER':'root',    <-----------------------
        'PASSWORD':'1234', <-----------------------
        'HOST':'127.0.0.1',
        'PORT':'3306',
        'OPTIONS': {'charset':'utf8mb4'},
    }
}

#views.py
conn = pymysql.connect('localhost',port=3306,「user='root',passwd='1234'」,charset='utf8',db='literature')


>>> cd ChineseLiterature/

>>> python manage.py runserver

Now, we can enjoy service by typing 「localhost:8000/bookInfo/」!
